$ docker volume ls

$ docker volume create docker-demo
docker-demo

$ docker volume inspect docker-demo
[
    {
        "CreatedAt": "2025-08-21T06:42:50Z",
        "Driver": "local",
        "Labels": null,
        "Mountpoint": "/var/lib/docker/volumes/docker-demo/_data",
        "Name": "docker-demo",
        "Options": null,
        "Scope": "local"
    }
]

$ docker volume rm <name of volume>
$ docker run -d --mount source=demo-volume,target=/app <image-name>   # here we are running a n image and also mounting a vloume to it. sourve is the name of volume and target is the directory in container where you want to copy the data from

Once the volume is mounted we can insect docker container and check 'Mounts' sectin there as below. If you want to add more firld values then you can add a comma after target in above command and keep adding field and its value.

Volume can be deleted only after deleting container attached to it.

"Mounts": [
            {
                "Type": "volume",
                "Name": "demo-volume",
                "Source": "/var/lib/docker/volumes/demo-volume/_data",
                "Destination": "/app",
                "Driver": "local",
                "Mode": "z",
                "RW": true,          # RW means read-write.
                "Propagation": ""
            }
        ],
